snippet.textDisplay:
HOW and WHY has no-one EVER THOUGHT OF THIS BEFORE!? Obviously this could have been done with "traditional" (internal combustion engine) vehicles, just with different differentials and different differential locks (for example: Instead of locking the "rear diff" so both wheels turn at the same speed, in the same gear-ratio and in the same direction; the "diffs" could be locked in a way where both wheels, on each axle, turn at the same speed, in the same gear-ratio, in opposite directions) as the way the wheels turn is irrelevant to how the vehicle is powered; the drive-train (gear box, propshaft, differentials etc.) could have EASILY been set up, to enable you to lock the differentials in a way where the wheels on the left-side of the vehicle turn in the opposite direction, the the wheels on the right-side of the vehicle.

I mean, how cool would that be on a Range Rover Sport, or a Porsche Cayenne Turbo, or an Audi Q9 RS!?

This is one of the coolest "features" I've seen on a car since, well, I can't remember; maybe since Audi invented the Quattro system!?

A different, but ETERNALLY SERIOUS subject:

Yahshua (Jesus) The Messiah Saves.

We are praying for ALL of you.

Peace and love, and prayers,

TJ & Mercy x
